===Noun===
'''résumé''' (''plural'' '''[[résumés]]''')
#a [[summary]]
#{{US}} A [[curriculum vitae]]; an [[account]] of one's [[employment]] [[history]] and [[qualification]]s (often for presentation to a [[potential]] future [[employer]] when applying for a job.)

====Synonyms====
#[[summary]], [[synopsis]]
#[[curriculum vitae]] (''UK''), [[CV]] (''UK''), [[summary]] (''US'')

<!--This usage not reflects the opinion of a few Wiktionarians, nobody else's. Improve or remove.
====Usage notes====
While some dispute the history, other Americans insist that the US way of spelling this term is [[resumé]], on the premise that the single accented version adheres to the long-time practice of accenting borrowed words to emphasize pronunciation, such as '''[[café]]''' and '''[[touché]]'''.  Others cite British dictionaries as evidence that '''résumé''' is the preferred spelling, despite the fact that British use (almost exclusively) the term [[CV]] for this meaning.  If submitting your summary in America to someone who is older, referring to it as your '''résumé''' may look odd to your prospective employer.  For younger employers, who have only ever seen it (perhaps incorrectly) "auto-corrected" by certain word-processing programs, '''resumé''' may seem better.-->

